race.comment: They'll go like the clappers in this. SCRIPTED (3) hasn't done much wrong with two wins and a second from three career outings and will strip fitter following that first-up effort after a lengthy spell. Looks the runner in this field with the most upside and rates the testing material against this lot. BARBERRY SPUR (5) is one from one over this six-furlong journey and will be ready to peak now third-up. Can feature from the favourable draw. ABENDER (2) has only missed the top-four spot once in eight career starts and rarely puts in a poor one. Has to be included. The well-related WHISPERING ROGUE (12) (half to 2xG2 winner and G1 placed Whispering Brook) has hit the frame in all five starts to date and is a must for the exotics players. SAXOBUSHI (10) is a last-start victor who shouldn't be underestimated.
